                "institute": "3CHPLNZ"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " ZF-300-II Intense Neutron Generator at",
                "Lanzhou University, the yield was about 3*e10~4*e10",
                "n/s."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The tritium-titanium (T-Ti) target used in the",
                "generator was 1.35 mg/cm2 thick. An effective",
                "deuteron beam energy was 135 KeV and a beam current",
                "was 500 micro-A."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "CH8403 coaxial high-purity germanium detector",
                "made in the People Republic of China, sensitive",
                "volume was 110 cm3, with a relative efficiency of 20%",
                "and an energy resolution of 3 KeV at 1332 KeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The groups of samples were placed at 0, 45, 90, 135",
                "degree angles relative to the beam direction. The",
                "samples in each group were sandwiched between two Al",
                "or two Nb foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
